+## Auto-retry budget persistence vs the healer's in-memory budget (2026-06-29)
+
+`Hive::Daemon::AutoRetry::StateStore` PERSISTS the per-`(project,slug,
+reason)` retry budget so a daemon restart does not silently re-clear a
+repeatedly-failing dependency marker (dependency markers can fail
+identically for hours, e.g. the Codex auth-401 case). This is an
+intentional divergence from [[modules/daemon#StaleAgentHealer]], whose
+budget is in-memory and re-arms on restart/SIGHUP. The exhausted audit
+event flags `budget_scope: "persisted"` and names `hive markers clear` as
+the reset gesture. If a future review prefers parity with the healer, the
+store can be downgraded to in-memory by deleting the JSON file — flagged
+here rather than in [[decisions]] because it is a known divergence, not a
+settled decision. See [[modules/auto_retry]].
