+---
+date: 2026-06-29
+slug: daemon-auto-retry-dependency-recovery-layer
+type: change
+tags: [daemon, auto-retry, recovery, healer]
+---
+
+## Add daemon auto-retry dependency-recovery layer
+
+Added `Hive::Daemon::AutoRetry` — a dependency-recovery layer that clears
+and re-dispatches parked terminal `ERROR` markers once the underlying
+dependency is verified healthy again, without ever touching unknown
+errors, business-logic failures, or markers where retry could discard user
+work. Sibling to [[modules/daemon#StaleAgentHealer]] (which keeps its
+environmental auto-clears).
+
+v1 allowlist (two reasons, each gated on a recognized diagnostic
+signature):
+
+- `implementer_failed` on 4-execute with a Codex auth-401 log signature
+  (after `codex login status` + `codex exec --json` smoke probes + a green
+  `hive doctor` precondition).
+- `claude_launch_failed` on a tmux-mode stage after the launcher
+  readiness probes (wrapper/detector/binary-version/doctor) pass.
+
+Mechanics identical to a manual `hive markers clear` + re-dispatch
+(re-run from start; no resume path). Bounded by a per-`(project, slug,
+reason)` retry budget of 2 with backoff (immediate, then 30 min) and a
+changed-health-signal gate (fingerprint inequality). Safety guard blocks
+retry when terminal success output exists, the worktree is dirty with
+out-of-scope residue, or answered brainstorm/plan user content would be
+overwritten; uncertain ⇒ do not retry. Audit on both the task
+`events.jsonl` and `daemon.log`; negative decisions throttled.
+
+Intentional divergence from the healer: the auto-retry budget is
+**persisted** (`daemon_auto_retry_state.json`, atomic write + fail-closed
+load) so a daemon restart does not silently re-clear a repeatedly-failing
+dependency marker; the exhausted event flags `budget_scope: "persisted"`
+and names `hive markers clear` as the reset gesture.
+
+Ships behind the global kill-switch `daemon.auto_retry.enabled` (default
+`true` for the v1 allowlisted reasons only).
+
+New files under `lib/hive/daemon/auto_retry/`: `classifier`, `probes`,
+`signal_fingerprint`, `probe_cache`, `budget`, `state_store`,
+`safety_guard`, `retry_executor`, `auditor`, `coordinator`, plus the
+namespace `auto_retry.rb`. Dispatcher + config wiring; closed-enum
+additions to `Logger::EVENTS` (`auto_retry_*`) and
+`Hive::Events::EVENT_TYPES` (`:auto_retry`).
+
+See [[modules/auto_retry]].
