@@ -0,0 +1,70 @@
+---
+title: Hive::Daemon::AutoRetry
+type: module
+source: lib/hive/daemon/auto_retry/
+created: 2026-06-29
+updated: 2026-06-29
+tags: [daemon, module, automation, auto-retry, recovery]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: Dependency-recovery auto-retry layer for parked terminal `ERROR`
+markers whose underlying dependency has recovered. A sibling to
+[[modules/daemon#StaleAgentHealer]]: the healer auto-clears a narrow
+*environmental* subset of markers (agent loss, `limits_reached` cooldown,
+`unpushed_commits`, side-effect-safe `timeout`, fix-phase auto-commit
+hiccups); `AutoRetry` adds recovery for two *dependency-shaped* failures
+that the healer intentionally does not touch, once a health probe confirms
+the dependency is healthy again and a safety guard confirms no user work
+would be discarded. Ships behind the global kill-switch
+`daemon.auto_retry.enabled` (default `true` for the v1 allowlisted reasons
+only).
+
+## Scope (v1)
+
+Only two recoverable reasons, each gated on a recognized diagnostic
+signature; everything else stays parked for manual `hive markers clear`:
+
+- `ERROR reason=implementer_failed` on **4-execute** when the stage log
+  carries a Codex auth-401 signature (`401`, `Missing bearer`, `Missing
+  basic`, `bearer/basic auth`). A `limits_reached`-classified
+  `implementer_failed` is excluded (the healer owns it).
+- `ERROR reason=claude_launch_failed` on any tmux-mode stage whose
+  launcher readiness probe now passes.
+
+Out of scope: a broad "transient" category, business/test/review/merge/
+dirty/unknown failures, a special resume path (re-run from start only),
+per-reason tuning, `gh`-driven probes, and (deliberate divergence from
+the healer) the retry budget is **persisted** so a daemon restart does
+not silently re-clear a repeatedly-failing dependency marker 2 more times.
+
+## Module map
+
+| Module | File | Purpose |
+|--------|------|---------|
+| `AutoRetry` | `lib/hive/daemon/auto_retry.rb` | Namespace + constants: `RECOVERABLE_REASONS`, `CODEX_AUTH_401_RE`, probe timeouts, `FALLBACK_PROBE_INTERVAL_SEC` (5 min), `MAX_AUTO_RETRIES` (2), backoffs (immediate then 30 min), capture bytes. |
+| `AutoRetry::Classifier` | `.../classifier.rb` | Pure: classify a parked `ERROR` row's marker attrs + bounded stage-log tail against the v1 signatures. Returns `{reason,signature,stage}` or `:unknown`. Excludes non-execute stages, headless launcher failures, `limits_reached` text, and every unknown reason. Degrades to `:unknown` on missing/garbage/oversized logs. |
+| `AutoRetry::Probes` | `.../probes.rb` | Timeout-bounded health probes returning a typed `Result` (name/status/stdout/stderr/duration/detail). `doctor_pass` (in-process, green iff no row missing/version_too_old), `codex_login_status` (in-process credential precheck + 10s `codex login status`), `codex_exec_smoke` (30s `codex exec --json`), `wrapper_exists`/`ready_detector`/`binary_version_match` (10s `claude --version` vs min). Shell-outs run under `Timeout` with a process-group kill; spawn errors→`:error`, timeouts→`:timeout`, never `:green`. The spawn runner and doctor are injectable so tests need no real codex/claude. |
+| `AutoRetry::SignalFingerprint` | `.../signal_fingerprint.rb` | Pure digest of coarse inputs that justify re-probing (claude.mode, agent bin paths, `CODEX_HOME`/`HIVE_*_BIN` env, codex login state + auth.json mtime, wrapper mtime, marker_id + state-file mtime). The "changed health signal since the last failed attempt" gate is fingerprint inequality. |
+| `AutoRetry::ProbeCache` | `.../probe_cache.rb` | Per-tick memo keyed by `(reason, fingerprint)` so parked markers do not re-spawn codex/claude every poll; cleared at the start of each tick by the coordinator. |
+| `AutoRetry::Budget` | `.../budget.rb` | Max 2 auto-retries per task/reason; changed signal required; immediate backoff after the first attempt, 30 min after the second; exhaust ⇒ permanent park. `allow?` returns `:allow`/`:exhausted`/`:unchanged_signal`/`:in_backoff`; `record_attempt!` runs only after a successful clear. |
+| `AutoRetry::StateStore` | `.../state_store.rb` | Persisted JSON store (`daemon_auto_retry_state.json`) of the per-`(project,slug,reason)` attempt record. Atomic write + fail-closed load (mirrors [[modules/daemon#DispatchBaselines]]). |
+| `AutoRetry::SafetyGuard` | `.../safety_guard.rb` | Never discard user work: blocks retry when an earlier `EXECUTE_COMPLETE` is present, when the execute worktree is dirty with out-of-scope residue (checked via `Hive::Stages::AutoCommit` scope allowlist), or when a brainstorm/plan launcher failure would overwrite answered user content (`BrainstormParser` answered-question check for 2-brainstorm, seed-only check for 3-plan). Uncertain ⇒ do not retry. |
+| `AutoRetry::RetryExecutor` | `.../retry_executor.rb` | Clear + re-enqueue, mechanically identical to `hive markers clear` + re-dispatch: `Hive::Markers.clear_current` with `reason`+`marker_id` match-attrs, re-enqueue via `DispatchRequestQueue` with the stage-appropriate verb, observe the pre-clear state-file mtime. A raced clear returns `:clear_failed` (no budget consumed); a failed requeue after a clear returns `:requeue_failed` with the manual remediation command. |
+| `AutoRetry::Auditor` | `.../auditor.rb` | Records decisions on both the task `events.jsonl` (`Hive::Events.emit :auto_retry`) and the daemon log (`Logger.event`), with the required fields. Negative decisions are throttled per rationale signature; exhaustion is logged once per key per process with `budget_scope: "persisted"` and the `hive markers clear` reset gesture. |
+| `AutoRetry::Coordinator` | `.../coordinator.rb` | Tick entry point: composes U1–U7, iterates recoverable `ERROR` rows after the healer and before per-row dispatch, with the same skip guards (legacy layout, `running_task?`, `live_task_lock`). |
+
+## Wiring
+
+The coordinator is constructed in `Hive::Daemon::Dispatcher` alongside
+`StaleAgentHealer`, called in `tick` **after** the healer in the same
+defensive rescue (an auto-retry bug cannot crash the tick / trip
+`StartLimitBurst`), and rebuilt on SIGHUP reload. The kill-switch reads
+`daemon.auto_retry.enabled` fresh every tick (default true) so a config
+flip takes effect within one tick. Ordering + reason disjointness prevent
+double-clear: the healer never clears `implementer_failed`/
+`claude_launch_failed`, and the classifier returns `:unknown` for the
+healer-owned reasons.
+
+See [[gaps]] for the intentional budget-persistence divergence from the
+healer's in-memory budget, and [[decisions]] for the fixed-allowlist
+design.
